==English==

===Noun===
'''professor''' (''plural:'' [[professors]])

# A teacher or faculty member at a college or university.
# A higher ranking for a teacher or faculty member at a college or university.
# North American professorial ranks differ from many other countries.
# I''Italic text''nternational prof''Italic text''essor can sometimes be used to designate expatriate
academics. Some independent scholars are sometimes globally peripatetic professors; sometimes more a researcher or lecturer professor, if attached to a university for a time; ususally for less than two years.Some tenured  and untenured professors, by choice, have come to adopt the informal title of International Professor: e.g. such a faculty member may connect to professors in other countries for collegiality,and research and scholarship collaborations. Increasingly apparent are the expat professors: Those who teach overseas for more than a year or two, are now sometimes adopting the appelation "international professor." International professors, also becoming more visable, are dual country/continent, dual appointment academics.

